This paper deals with the application of temporal logic to hybrid dynamical systems, which are systems that combine continuous and discrete dynamics. This topic is relevant to several areas of computer science, including control systems (cs.SY), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and robotics (cs.RO). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
